I"_<p><a href="/authors/ebeling">Johann Ebeling</a>, in his <a href="/sources/pauli_gerhardi"><em>Pauli Gerhardi Geistliche Andachten</em></a>, composed an original four-part musical setting for Gerhardt’s “Nun laßt uns gehn und treten.” The new tune ended up being used very little by churches, possibly due to the growing acceptance of <a href="/tunes/nun-lasst-uns"><span style="font-variant:small-caps;">nun lasst uns gott, dem herren</span></a> made popular by <a href="/authors/crüger">Johann Crüger</a>. Even Ebeling himself offered the option to sing the text with this tune in his book.</p>

